<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Michael Arkush and Tris Wykes and Jeannette Regalado 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 LANDING: Poor weather in Florida caused the Space Shuttle Discovery to land at 
Edwards Air Force Base near Lancaster on Tuesday (B1), creating a sonic boom 
heard throughout the Valley. . . . But Edwards faces an uncertain future. Once 
the showcase home for the U.S. rocket program, it now faces stiff competition 
for scarce defense dollars. One rival: the Navy's Patuxent River flight test 
center in Maryland. 
</P>
<P>
 SHAKEN: The sonic boom scared the heck out of some people, including one 
frightened woman who whispered to an Antelope Valley sheriff's deputy that 
someone was breaking into her house. She was chagrined when Deputy Charles 
Marritt told her the truth. . . . Yet she was not alone. Foothill Division 
officers received about 100 calls. 
</P>
<P>
 SKATING TIPS: Gretzky may be the Great One. But Glantz could be the one the 
Los Angeles Kings need just as sorely. He's Rob Glantz (above), a Birmingham 
High grad who teaches a more efficient way to skate -- called power skating -- 
to the Kings at their Iceoplex camp in North Hills (C1). . . . "The little 
things Robbie says make sense right off the bat," said veteran Marty McSorley. 
</P>
<P>
 PUBLICITY HOUND: Ashley Whippet was a dog with a talent for catching Frisbees. 
Irv Lander, of Van Nuys, was a man with a talent for promotion. Twenty years 
ago, they started "canine Frisbee," and it's still going strong (B1). . . . 
Fame has its price, however: During a White House visit, Ashley had to ward off 
an attack by Billy Carter's mutt over the use of a water dish. 
</P>
<P>
 SHOTS: It's that season again. No, not fall. . . . Flu. But you can do 
something about it. Today's Valley Briefing (B14) explains how to combat the 
common cold and influenza, and where seniors can get free shots. . . . Daniel 
W. Martin, of the Los Angeles County Immunization Program, says it's too early 
to determine whether this flu season will be mild or severe. Michael Arkush and 
Tris Wykes and Jeannette Regalado 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
