SOCCER; FRENCH UNVEIL '98 WORLD CUP LOGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two months after World Cup '94 ended in the Rose Bowl, French organizers 
unveiled the logo for soccer's 1998 World Cup to be held in their country. 
"It's our calling card . . . our trademark for four years," said Michel 
Platini, a former French national team captain and coach. 
</P>
