<P>
 The Milwaukee Brewers announced that 30 full-time employees would be laid off 
because of the players' strike. Some of the layoffs will be permanent, said Tom 
Gausden, director of administration and human resources. . . . In a meeting 
that reaffirmed player solidarity but broke no new ground, union head Donald 
Fehr met with 33 players representing 19 teams in a nearly 3 1/2-hour session 
in Atlanta, the first of a seven-city tour. 
</P>
