<HEADLINE>
<P>
FISHING REPORT: IT'S A VERY COOL TIME TO GET TROUT IN SIERRA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It's the most beautiful time of year in the Eastern Sierra, with trees in full 
bloom coloring the landscape in a various shades of yellow and red. 
</P>
<P>
 But for some, this is merely a bonus. After a fairly dormant summer, trout 
have responded to cooler temperatures throughout the region. 
</P>
<P>
 Grant Lake along the June Loop produced two of the best catches: a 4-pound 
8-ounce brown trout by Adam Vick of Fullerton and a 4-6 brown by John Johnson 
of Napa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
