<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; POLICE ASSOCIATION BACKS 5 CANDIDATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Port Hueneme Police Officers Assn. has endorsed five of the 14 candidates 
running for three City Council seats in the November election. 
</P>
<P>
 Saying the candidates will work to maintain the Police Department, the 
association endorsed Valorie Morrison, Frank McElfish Jr., Tony Volante, David 
Goodman and Robert Turner. 
</P>
<P>
 McElfish, Morrison and Volante intensively campaigned for the June ballot 
initiative intended to keep the Police Department from being disbanded and law 
enforcement services contracted through the Sheriff's Department, association 
President Kenneth Dobbe said. 
</P>
<P>
 The other two candidates, Goodman and Turner, were recommended to the 
association by the Friends of Our Port Hueneme Police Department Political 
Action Committee, which has endorsed all five candidates. 
</P>
<P>
 The candidates are running for council seats that will be vacant as three 
incumbents step down. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
