<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; RV RESORT PROPOSAL TO GET ANOTHER LOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Port Hueneme City Council will consider tonight whether to drop a plan to 
build a recreational vehicle resort on a city-owned beach, or redesign the 
proposal and resubmit it to the California Coastal Commission. 
</P>
<P>
 The Coastal Commission rejected the city's 144-space project last Wednesday 
because members considered the beachfront site an environmentally sensitive 
plant and wildlife habitat. 
</P>
<P>
 City Manager Richard Velthoen said another option is to postpone action until 
a newly constituted council takes office in January. Three of the five council 
seats are on the November ballot. 
</P>
<P>
 But Mayor Orvene Carpenter said he believes the council should proceed with 
the project. 
</P>
<P>
 "I am a firm believer that we should try to continue to purse the RV resort so 
we can have a source of money," Carpenter said. CHRISTINA LIMA 
</P>
</TEXT>
