<P>
GLENDALE / BURBANK FOCUS: BURBANK; LITERACY PROGRAM SEEKS VOLUNTEERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE RYFLE 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Burbank Public Library's literacy program is seeking volunteers interested 
in tutoring English-speaking adults who need help with their reading skills. 
</P>
<P>
 There are no special credentials or qualifications needed to become a tutor 
other than competent reading skills.However, interested volunteers must attend 
a series of three training and orientation sessions beginning Thursday from 7 
to 8:45 p.m. The second and third sessions will be held Saturday and Oct. 1, 
from 10:15 a.m. to 4:15 p.m., with a break for lunch. 
</P>
<P>
 The sessions will be at the Burbank Main Library, 110 N. Glenoaks Blvd., on 
the second floor. 
</P>
<P>
 About 30 people have signed up for the classes so far, but organizers said 
more tutors are needed. For information, call (818) 953-9727. STEVE RYFLE 
</P>
