DIGEST; FORD IS HIRED AS NORTHRIDGE SOFTBALL ASSISTANT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Kelly Ford has been hired to assist Cal State Northridge softball Coach Janet 
Sherman. 
</P>
<P>
 Ford, who played for Oklahoma in 1990 and '92, returns to the Matador program 
after a one-year absence.Ford was a graduate assistant in 1993 to former Coach 
Gary Torgeson. She was an assistant at Oklahoma last season. 
</P>
<P>
 "She knows how the program is run and she knows the expectations here," 
Sherman said. "We also have the same goals and I know she is going to put out 
100%." Football  
</P>
<P>
 Antelope Valley High's Caleb Smith did not suffer a broken right foot as 
originally thought after last week's victory over West Bakersfield. However, 
the senior defensive lineman was unable to practice Monday, and his status for 
this weekend's game against Bakersfield is uncertain, Antelope Valley Coach 
Brent Newcomb said. 
</P>
