fumble with a minute left that secured the Lancers' victory. "I was expecting a 
big year because I knew I wasn't going to have to share the ball with another 
tailback like last year," Smith said. "Our offensive line has also improved. 
When you're running behind a line that has two 320-pounders. . . . and a 
(6-foot, 190-pound) fullback like Marcel Decir, you get some holes to run 
through. But I didn't expect this type of yardage." 
