<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LITTLE BIT OF HISTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Cal Lutheran played the only National Assn. of Intercollegiate Athletics 
football game to be nationally televised.The Kingsmen beat Westminster, 30-14, 
for the NAIA championship in December, 1971. NBC aired the game because of a 
scheduling quirk that left the network with no other college games. Ross Porter 
and Tom Hawkins were the announcers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA092194-0108 </DOCNO>
