<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL / DAILY REPORT; RAMS; MILLER'S AVAILABILITY QUESTIONABLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ram quarterback Chris Miller, who has a sore shoulder and ribs, will not throw 
in practice today, raising more questions about his status for Sunday's game at 
Kansas City. 
</P>
<P>
 "(Backup quarterback Chris) Chandler will get the work that Miller usually 
gets," Coach Chuck Knox said. 
</P>
<P>
 Third-string quarterback Tommy Maddox, who has run the scout squad and was 
inactive for the first three games, will work with the top offensive units as a 
backup for the first time. The Rams traded a fourth-round draft pick to the 
Denver Broncos Aug. 27 to get Maddox, a former UCLA standout. 
</P>
<P>
 "Tommy has a live arm and is an accurate thrower," Knox said. "He has picked 
up the knowledge of the offense very, very well." 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams, seeking a receiver to replace an injured Richard Buchanan, are 
expected to re-sign Todd Kinchen today. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams cut Kinchen, a third-year pro, on Sept. 6 to make room for cornerback 
Darryl Henley. 
</P>
<P>
 Coaches worked Kinchen out Tuesday at Rams Park in hopes he can replace 
Buchanan, sidelined two to three weeks because of a pulled hamstring. 
</P>
<P>
 Kinchen, who recently had a tryout in Miami, had suffered a pulled hamstring 
before the start of the season but was cleared to practice the day he was cut. 
</P>
<P>
 If Kinchen signs, the Rams probably will free a roster spot by placing left 
guard Keith Loneker, who suffered a fallen left arch against Atlanta, on the 
injured-reserve list. MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
