<TEXT>
<P>
 New Balance Faces False-Advertising Charges: The Federal Trade Commission said 
in an administrative complaint that commercials boasting that New Balance 
athletic shoes are made in America are misleading because a substantial number 
of shoes are made in foreign countries. New Balance is disputing the 
allegations.The company said some shoes are produced in the United States while 
others are made in foreign countries. The company said the country of origin is 
clearly stated on each product. Separately, Hyde Athletic Shoes Inc., makers of 
shoes under the Saucony, Playskool and Barbie brand names, settled charges that 
advertisements claiming its products are made in America mislead consumers. 
Hyde neither confirmed nor denied the allegations and said it settled to avoid 
expensive litigation. 
