<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: SUN VALLEY; ALARCON, RESIDENTS TO STUDY ECONOMIC PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANTONIO OLIVO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles City Councilman Richard Alarcon has scheduled two information 
sessions this week for Sun Valley residents on the Los Angeles Neighborhood 
Initiative (LANI), a nonprofit organization assembled through Mayor Richard 
Riordan's office that explores economic development opportunities in blighted 
areas. 
</P>
<P>
 Along with members of the Sun Valley Recognized Community Organization, a 
division of LANI made up of business people and community leaders, Alarcon will 
field questions and solicit suggestions from residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The meetings are scheduled today at 7 p.m. and Sunday at noon in the Sun 
Valley Recreation Center, 8133 Vineland Ave. 
</P>
<P>
 The objective of LANI is to benefit economically disadvantaged 
transit-dependent communities by revitalizing public spaces and promoting 
business along major city streets and transportation corridors. LANI is funded 
by the U.S. Department of Transportation through the Los Angeles Metropolitan 
Transportation Authority. ANTONIO OLIVO 
</P>
