 Fire gutted a two-story house surrounded by dry brush Tuesday morning, causing 
$300,000 in damage, the Los Angeles County Fire Department reported. 
</P>
<P>
 People from as far away as two miles saw the flames at the house in the 3500 
block of Poppy Drive near Mulholland Highway and thought it was a brush fire, 
said Fire Inspector Bob Brandelli. 
