<HEADLINE>
<P>
SERIES OF 5 AFTERSHOCKS JOLT CALIFORNIA-NEVADA BORDER AREA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A burst of aftershock activity occurred in the area of last week's strong 
earthquake on the California-Nevada border southeast of Lake Tahoe, with five 
moderate jolts ranging from magnitude 3.9 to 4.6 in a 12-hour period, 
seismologists reported Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The National Earthquake Information Center at Golden, Colo., said the 
strongest of the aftershocks was felt at 10:17 p.m. Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 The new earthquakes caused no injuries, but some items were thrown off shelves 
at Gardnerville, Nev., on U.S. 395. 
</P>
