<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: CENTRAL; WESTMINSTER; EX-PRINCIPAL WILL BE HONORED THIS 
WEEK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two events honoring former Willis Warner Middle School Principal Joan Read 
will be held this week, a school district spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 Read, 62, retired recently after almost 40 years with the Westminster School 
District, where she served as teacher and principal on several campuses, 
district spokeswoman Audrey Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 During Read's last year as principal at Warner, the school won a Golden Bell 
Award for its language arts program. The award is the highest honor bestowed by 
the California School Boards Assn., Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 Warner will host an assembly at 12:15 p.m. today, which will be open to the 
public. Between 2 to 4 p.m., the school will host a community tea to honor Read 
in the school multipurpose room, Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
 On Friday, friends and community members will hold a $30-a-plate dinner in her 
honor. The dinner will be at Seacliff Country Club, 6501 Palm Ave., in 
Huntington Beach. 
</P>
<P>
 For more information, call (714) 898-2378.JON NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA092194-0240 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 081341 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
September 21, 1994, Wednesday, Orange County Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
Metro; Part B; Page 2; Column 4; Orange County Focus 
</P>
</SECTION>
<LENGTH>
<P>
