<P>
PRO FOOTBALL DAILY REPORT; RAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MIKE REILLEY 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Tailback Jerome Bettis has gained 206 yards in 45 carries the past two weeks 
against Atlanta and San Francisco.But he has barely touched the ball in the 
second half, when the Rams are passing and trying to get back in the game. 
</P>
<P>
 Bettis gained 26 yards in six carries in the second half against Atlanta after 
gaining 76 yards in 18 carries in the first half. In the second half against 
San Francisco, he had 34 yards in only four carries after rushing for 70 yards 
in 17 carries in the first half. 
</P>
<P>
 The Rams are 2-7 in games in which Bettis has run for more than 100 yards, 
beating New Orleans and Chicago last season. MIKE REILLEY 
