<HEADLINE>
<P>
AMERICA WEST, CONTINENTAL OFFER DISCOUNTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CHRIS WOODYARD, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two airlines announced a round of leisure travel fare reductions Tuesday that 
could cut the price of some tickets for Southern California passengers by 
nearly half, but customers must act quickly. 
</P>
<P>
 America West Airlines is offering fares reduced by as much as 48% through Dec. 
20, but travelers have only until Friday to buy their tickets.The reductions 
require a 14-day advance purchase and a Friday night stay. The deepest 
discounts are available on Mondays through Thursdays. 
</P>
<P>
 Continental Airlines also said Tuesday that it will offer discounts on ticket 
sales through Friday to inaugurate new service starting Oct. 30, including a 
route from John Wayne Airport in Orange County to Newark, N.J. The limited time 
fare for that route will be $318 round trip. 
</P>
<P>
 The America West discounts cut the round trip fare from Los Angeles to Chicago 
by 11% to $338, and from Las Vegas to Atlanta by 48% to $198. Rival airlines 
usually have matched the America West reductions in cities where they compete. 
</P>
<P>
 America West has offered discounts so often this year that they are receiving 
less attention from travel agents. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's the sale that will never go away," said Thom Nulty, president of 
Associated Travel Management in Santa Ana. "It appears to work for them. . . . 
Consumers are conditioned to wait for a sale." 
</P>
</TEXT>
