<P>
 Ropak Corp.: Shares of the plastic container maker continued to climb in price 
Tuesday, reaching a new 52-week high of $9. 
</P>
<P>
 Ropak stock was up more than 8%, or 69 cents a share, in very heaving Nasdaq 
trading. About 258,900 shares changed hands Tuesday, compared with an average 
daily volume of 11,700 shares. The Fullerton company's previous 52-week high of 
$8.50 a share was reached on Aug. 26. 
</P>
<P>
 Ronald Cameron, chief financial officer for Ropak, said an analyst for Orange 
County's largest investment banking firm, Cruttenden & Co. in Irvine, visited 
Ropak on Friday. Cruttenden bought about 10,000 Ropak shares on Monday and at 
least 5,000 shares Tuesday, a trader at the company said. 
</P>
