<P>
 Campaign debate -- An article in Tuesday's editions did not fully explain 
Republican Gov. Pete Wilson's proposal for choosing a panel of questioners for 
a possible debate with state Treasurer Kathleen Brown, the Democratic 
challenger. Wilson proposed that he and Brown each draw up a list of 10 
acceptable political reporters. Names that appeared on both lists would be 
placed in a hat, and three would be chosen at random. 
</P>
